SUMMARIZER="H">

At a memorial service at Norfolk Naval Air Station Monday for the 47 Battleship Iowa 
crewmen who perished in an explosion, President Bush spoke to 6000 mourners crowded 
into a hangar. Outside 2000 listened on loudspeakers. 45 victims' families attended. 500 
Iowa crewmen were blocked by traffic and Bush security. Iowa commander Capt. Fred 
Moosally praised the turret's gun crew as the best on the ship. The guns had been 
thoroughly inspected the morning of the accident. The surviving crew in the turret's 
powder magazine, waiting for the gun to fire, evacuated when no one answered the 
interior communications link.</SUM>
